**Abstract:** Detailed reading notes on Hastings Rashdall's "The Universities of Europe in the Middle Ages" (1895). Covers the twelfth century renaissance, Abelard's role in founding scholastic theology, the controversy over universals, the decline of classical literary culture after Aristotle's dominance, the rise of the Mendicant orders (Dominicans and Franciscans) at Paris, the prohibition and later acceptance of Aristotle's physical and metaphysical works, and the structure of theological education based on Bible and Sentences.
